I"<p>To combine (“<em>squash</em>”) multiple commits into a single commit, use <code class="highlighter-rouge">git rebase -i &lt;$AFTER_THIS_COMMIT_ID&gt;</code>.</p>

<p>In the editor, replace every <em>pick</em> with <em>squash</em>, <strong>except</strong> the first one!</p>

<p>To overwrite the Git history on a remote, use <code class="highlighter-rouge">git push -f origin master</code> to force the push.</p>

